---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'About BreederHQ', url: '/about' }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About BreederHQ - Professional Breeding Management Software"
  description="BreederHQ is the all-in-one breeding management platform built for professional animal breeders. Learn about our mission, team, and why we built BreederHQ."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>

  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-gray-50 py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-6">
          About BreederHQ
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          BreederHQ is professional breeding management software built by people who understand the realities of running a breeding program.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Mission -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Professional breeders deserve professional tools. BreederHQ was founded to replace the patchwork of spreadsheets, paper records, and disconnected apps that breeders have relied on for years. We believe that when breeders have the right software, the entire industry benefits: healthier animals, more transparent programs, and better experiences for buyers.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          BreederHQ is the only platform where breeders manage their complete breeding programs on-platform, from pedigree tracking and genetics analysis to client portals and marketplace listings, creating a level of transparency and verification that listing-only sites cannot match.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why We Built BreederHQ -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Why We Built BreederHQ</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          The breeding industry doesn't have a software problem. It has a data problem. Every tool a breeder adds makes it worse.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Pedigrees live in a registry site. Health records are in a spreadsheet. Payments go through Venmo or QuickBooks. Buyer communication happens over Instagram DMs. The medication schedule is on a whiteboard in the barn or kennel. Finding a good transporter means asking around in a Facebook group. Selling an animal means listing it on yet another site that knows nothing about your program.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Every one of those tools is a dead end. The data goes in and never comes back out. None of it connects. None of it builds on itself. Your medication history doesn't inform your breeding decisions. Your financial data doesn't tell you which lines are most profitable. Your buyer feedback never loops back into your program. And every time you add another tool to solve another one-off problem, you're adding another silo that makes the whole picture harder to see.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          There's an even bigger gap. No platform connects breeders, buyers, and service providers in one place. Breeders know which trainers, transporters, and vets are the best. Service providers know which breeders run the most professional programs. Buyers want to find both. But all of that knowledge is trapped in private conversations, closed Facebook groups, and word of mouth. There's no shared ecosystem where everyone benefits from being connected.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          BreederHQ exists to fix all of it. When your breeding plans, health records, genetics, finances, buyer relationships, and marketplace listings all live in one place, the data actually works for you. Your vet gets a health report generated from real records, not something you pieced together from three apps. Your marketplace listings are backed by verified health testing, calculated COI scores, and documented breeding history. Your breeding decisions are informed by everything you've ever tracked, not just what you can remember. And the breeders, buyers, and service providers on the platform create a network where everyone gets better because they're connected.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What BreederHQ Does -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What BreederHQ Does</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Breeding Program Management</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              BreederHQ provides pedigree tracking with automatic COI calculation, breeding cycle management with species-specific timelines, and 8-phase breeding plan lifecycle tracking from planning through placement.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Genetics & Health Tools</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Advanced genetics tools in BreederHQ include multi-locus coat color tracking, offspring genetics simulation, best match finder algorithms, and comprehensive health testing record management for OFA, PennHIP, and genetic panels.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Client Portal & Communication</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              BreederHQ gives your clients 24/7 portal access with invoicing, Stripe payments, e-signature agreements, direct messaging, and document sharing, providing a professional experience that builds trust.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Marketplace & Discovery</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              The BreederHQ marketplace connects verified breeders with serious buyers. Earned trust badges (Verified, Health Tested, Quick Responder, Experienced, and Trusted) cannot be bought, only earned through documented behavior.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Multi-Species -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Built for Multiple Species</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          BreederHQ supports professional breeders of <a href="/dogs" class="text-primary hover:underline">dogs</a>, <a href="/cats" class="text-primary hover:underline">cats</a>, <a href="/horses" class="text-primary hover:underline">horses</a>, <a href="/goats" class="text-primary hover:underline">goats</a>, <a href="/alpacas" class="text-primary hover:underline">alpacas</a>, <a href="/llamas" class="text-primary hover:underline">llamas</a>, <a href="/rabbits" class="text-primary hover:underline">rabbits</a>, <a href="/sheep" class="text-primary hover:underline">sheep</a>, and <a href="/cattle" class="text-primary hover:underline">cattle</a>. Each species gets tools tailored to its specific breeding cycles, health testing protocols, and genetics tracking requirements.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          Whether you breed one species or several, BreederHQ adapts to the way you work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Connect -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Connect with BreederHQ</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Follow BreederHQ for product updates, breeding industry insights, and early access announcements.
        </p>
